Kenneth Morton GUTNICK, Petitioner, v. IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION SERVICE, Respondent. No. 28932

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 16, 1970. *1129Ruben Montemayor, San Antonio, Tex., for petitioner. John N. Mitchell, Atty. Gen. of the U. S., Dept. of Justice, Washington, D. C. Troy A. Adams, Jr., Director, U. S. Immigration & Nat. Service, New Orleans, La., Seagal V. Wheatley, U. S. Atty., San Antonio, Tex., for respondent.

Before JOHN R. BROWN, Chief Judge, and MORGAN and INGRAHAM, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

Review denied. See Local Rule 21.1

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 430 F.2d 906 (5th Cir. 1970).

. Rule 18, 5th Cir.; See Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et al., 5th Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.
